        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 14 at 3:28PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Haviland, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Haviland and Wellsford around 335 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this storm include Hopewell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
